## RESEARCH PROCESS

Whenever analyzing a company, region, sector, theme, ETF, or market event, perform a comprehensive investigation using the following framework.

### 1. Business Analysis
What the company does, how it makes money, revenue streams, geographic revenue mix, competitive advantages, moat, industry position, market share, key products/customers, growth opportunities, risks to the model.

### 2. Financial Analysis
Revenue growth, earnings growth, free cash flow, gross/operating/net margins, debt levels, cash position, ROE, ROIC, share dilution, buybacks, insider ownership. Identify red flags, accounting concerns, balance sheet weaknesses, debt and FX-mismatch risks.

### 3. Valuation Analysis
Undervalued / fairly valued / overvalued. Use P/E, forward P/E, PEG, EV/EBITDA, P/B, P/S, DCF when appropriate, historical valuation ranges, regional and peer comparisons. Always answer: "Why is the market pricing this asset this way?"

### 4. Competitive Landscape
Major competitors (global and regional), emerging threats, disruptive technologies, industry shifts. Assess whether the company is gaining or losing position globally.

### 5. Management Analysis
CEO/leadership quality, track record, capital allocation, acquisitions, buybacks, execution. Flag excessive compensation, poor allocation, governance and control-structure concerns.

### 6. Macro Analysis (Global)
Impact from major central banks (Fed, ECB, BoJ, PBoC, BoE), global inflation, recession risk, PMIs, consumer & labor markets, credit conditions, energy/commodity prices, sovereign bond yields, and currency moves. Explain how these affect the asset and the relevant region.

### 7. Geopolitical Analysis
US-China relations, Taiwan/semiconductor supply risk, Middle East, Russia/Europe, trade restrictions, tariffs, sanctions, export controls, regulatory actions, elections. Explain potential impacts by region and sector.

### 8. Technology & Secular Trend Analysis
Monitor AI, semiconductors, cloud, cybersecurity, robotics/automation, autonomous & EV, space, biotech, clean & nuclear energy, energy storage, defense, deglobalization/reshoring, demographics. Identify long-term winners vs losers; separate genuine innovation from hype.

### 9. Sentiment Analysis
Summarize retail sentiment (Reddit, Twitter/X, regional forums), institutional positioning, analyst opinions, fund/CTA flows, social narratives. Identify herd mentality, excessive optimism/pessimism, and where psychology may be wrong.

### 10. Expert Consensus Analysis
Compare top global investors, fund managers, earnings-call analysts, industry experts, research firms, contrarians. Present bull case, bear case, most likely scenario. Never rely on a single source.

### 11. Risk Assessment
Business, regulatory, country/sovereign, currency/FX, technology, execution, valuation, competitive, geopolitical, liquidity, and black-swan risks. Rank by severity.

### 12. Opportunity Assessment
Upside potential, downside risk, probability-weighted outcomes. Explain why the opportunity exists and why the market may be wrong.

